{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/after-five-months-storybook/","webpackCompilationHash":"4e1985a14b92e7367e74","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":":heart: React","author":"Metamn"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"25b3a320-0b41-5419-854f-f43ceafac0de","excerpt":"Shiny new features on the way!","html":"<p>Shiny new features on the way!</p>\n<!--more-->\n<hr>\n<p><strong>This is the first post in a series of three.</strong></p>\n<p>A hiatus can introduce pain in restarting work on old projects. Frameworks change quickly. Now let’s see how the React ecosystem handles this.</p>\n<p>I have <a href=\"/react/after-five-months-react\">React</a>, <a href=\"/react/after-five-months-gatsby\">Gatsby</a> and Storybook projects to update and work on them again.</p>\n<hr>\n<h3>Storybook</h3>\n<p>It had a major update from <code class=\"language-text\">v4.x</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">v5.0</code>. Updates ending in 0 are usually unstable. I rather would wait for let’s say <code class=\"language-text\">v5.0.12</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">v5.1</code>.</p>\n<p>Updating the Storybook package for <a href=\"http://metamn.io/mr-ui\">MR-UI</a> was easy. Kudos to the SB team! It took secs.</p>\n<p>Cleaning up the old code took a few hours. Some addons had to be reconfigured, others became core features. The process was enjoyable since it was trimming code and make it more elegant, readable.</p>\n<p>The result? Not sure. The old Storybook was more flexible on theming and with some tweaks produced a more enjoyable experience.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/0309e/old-storybook.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The old Storybook\"\n        title=\"The old Storybook\"\n        src=\"/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/5cc77/old-storybook.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/72cd8/old-storybook.png 192w,\n/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/45483/old-storybook.png 384w,\n/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/5cc77/old-storybook.png 768w,\n/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/04090/old-storybook.png 1152w,\n/react/static/84f4a593eb9048f20afd81302007b12f/0309e/old-storybook.png 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The new Storybook officially supports theming which is more restrictive. Less tweaking more uniform looking.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 768px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/0309e/new-storybook.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The new Storybook\"\n        title=\"The new Storybook\"\n        src=\"/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/5cc77/new-storybook.png\"\n        srcset=\"/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/72cd8/new-storybook.png 192w,\n/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/45483/new-storybook.png 384w,\n/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/5cc77/new-storybook.png 768w,\n/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/04090/new-storybook.png 1152w,\n/react/static/fad3da5dae6f4fb5420e6b14e807e612/0309e/new-storybook.png 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Which is not a problem. With major upgrades no one can expect unofficial tweaks will be supported. And probably the strength of Storybook doesn’t lie in it’s theming support.</p>\n<p>What really pleased me is <a href=\"https://medium.com/storybookjs/storybook-docs-sneak-peak-5be78445094a\">Storybook Docs</a>. Which is still in … <code class=\"language-text\">v0.0</code>. With little patience, however, we will probably have a proper Design System tool based on stories. Wow! I’ll wait for it.</p>\n<p><strong>Verdict</strong></p>\n<p>As expected, a lot can happen in five months. I’ve lost customizations done with hard-labor but got some shiny new features I’ve always wanted.</p>\n<h3>Resources</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/storybookjs/storybook-docs-sneak-peak-5be78445094a\">Storybook Docs</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"After five months — Storybook","date":"May 08, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/after-five-months-storybook/","previous":{"excerpt":"New techniques for old problems.","fields":{"slug":"/react-inspired-bem-scss-styling/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"React inspired BEM / SCSS styling"}},"next":{"excerpt":"We couldn’t have better news. Lean code. Official stack. Strong leader.","fields":{"slug":"/after-five-months-react/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"After five months — React"}}}}}